\begin_layout Standard
It might seem interesting that the angle of repose does exist independent
 of the dimensions of the heap.
 Some have argued that the angle of repose might dependent upon the ratio
 of the grain size to the dimensions of the base.
 The aim of this experiment is to find the value of angle of repose as a
 function of the radius of the base.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Procedure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Grain particles (roughly of the order of 1.5 mm - 2mm diameter) are heaped
 into a pile on a disc of known diameter.
 The height of the pile is measured using a traveling microscope.
 The height is plotted for various values of disc size.
 The slope of the graph gives the angle of repose.
 
\end_layout

